              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nAPPEAL,CLOSED,INTERPRETER\n\nU.S. District Court\nEastern District of California - Live System (Fresno)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 1:20-cr-00252-JLT-BAM All Defendants\n\nCase title: USA v. Gastelo Date Filed: 12/17/2020\n\nMagistrate judge case number: 1:20-mj-00143-SKO Date Terminated: 11/17/2025\n\nAssigned to: District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston\nReferred to: Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe\nAppeals court case number: 25-7471 USCA, Ninth Circuit\n\nDefendant (1)\nMonico Gastelo represented by Andrea Renee St. Julian\nTERMINATED: 11/17/2025 Andrea St. Julian\nalso known as 12636 High Bluff Dr., Ste. 400\nMonico Erich Gastelo San Diego, CA 92130\nTERMINATED: 11/17/2025 858-792-6366\nFax: 858-792-6069\nEmail: arstjulian@icloud.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\n\nRoger Nuttall\nNuttall & Coleman\n2333 Merced St.\nFresno, CA 93721\n559-233-2900\nFax: 559-485-3852\nEmail: roger@nuttallcoleman.com\nTERMINATED: 12/29/2022\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\n\nRoger Dale Wilson\nLaw Office of Roger D Wilson\n2300 Tulare Street\nSuite 250\nFresno, CA 93721\n559-233-4100\nEmail: roger@wilson-law.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\n\nPending Counts Disposition\n18 U.S.C. 2251(a) and (c) - Sexual Exploitation of a Minor and\nCUSTODY: 300 months CONSECUTIVE. Special Assessment\nAttempt\n$100. SUPERVISED RELEASE: 180 months CONCURRENT.\n(1)\n18 U.S.C. 2252(a)(2) and (b)(1) - Receipt and Distribution of a\nVisual Depiction of a Minor Engaged in Sexually Explicit CUSTODY: 180 months CONSECUTIVE. Special Assessment\nConduct $100. SUPERVISED RELEASE: 180 months CONCURRENT.\n(2)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\nNone\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nNone\n\nComplaints Disposition\n18:2251(a) and (e) -Sexual Exploitation of a Minor and\nAttempt;18:2252(a)(2)- Certain activities relating to material\ninvolving the sexual exploitation of minors including the receipt\nand/or distribution of child pornography; 18:2422(b) -\nAttempted Coercion and Enticement of a minor to Engage in\nIllegal Sexual Activity\n\nPlaintiff\nUSA represented by Fresno Forfeiture Unit\nUnited States Attorney's Office, Fresno\n2500 Tulare Street\nSuite 4401\nFresno, CA 93721\n559-497-4000\nEmail: usacae.ecffrsfor@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant US Attorney\n\nDavid L Gappa , GOVT\nUnited States Attorney's Office, Fresno\n2500 Tulare Street\nSuite 4401\nFresno, CA 93721\n(559) 497-4020\nFax: (559) 497-4099\nEmail: David.Gappa@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant US Attorney\n\nMcKenzie Hightower , GOVT\nDOJ-Crm\n1301 New York Ave. NW\nWashington, DC 20530\n202-215-7126\nEmail: mckenzie.hightower2@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\n\nDate Filed # Docket Text\n12/08/2020 1 CRIMINAL COMPLAINT as to Monico Erich Gastelo (2). (Martin-Gill, S) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/08/2020)\n12/09/2020 3 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held via video conference before Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone: INITIAL APPEARANCE\nRE CRIMINAL COMPLAINT as to Monico Erich Gastelo held on 12/9/2020. Defense counsel and defendant consent to appearing by\nvideoconference. The Court advised the defendant of the charges, rights, waived reading. Detention Hearing set for 12/10/2020 at 2:00 pm\nbefore Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone. Preliminary Examination set for 12/17/2020 at 02:00 PM in Courtroom 9 (SAB) before\nMagistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone. The defendant is temporarily detained pending the next hearing. The court instructed government\ncounsel under Rule 5(f) to comply with its disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Government Counsel: David Gappa via video.\nDefense Counsel: Roger Nuttall via video. Custody Status: (C) via video. Court Reporter/CD Number: R Lundy and ECRO M Hernandez\nvia video. (Hernandez, M) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/10/2020)\n12/10/2020 4 ORDER (TEXT ONLY) signed by Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone on 12/9/2020 as to defendant Monico Erich Gastelo: Pursuant to\nthe Due Process Protections Act, the court hereby orders counsel for the government to satisfy its discovery and disclosure obligations,\nincluding but not limited to its obligations under Brady v. Maryland, 373 U.S. 83 (1963), and its progeny. Failure to do so may result in\nconsequences such as the dismissal of the indictment or information, dismissal of individual charges, exclusion of evidence or witnesses,\nadverse jury instructions, contempt proceedings, and sanctions by the court. (Hernandez, M) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/10/2020)\n12/10/2020 5 SHACKLING MINUTE ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone on 12/10/2020: Monico Erich Gastelo is (USM # 21190-\n509). (Hernandez, M) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/10/2020)\n12/10/2020 6 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held via video conference before Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone: DETENTION HEARING\nas to Monico Erich Gastelo held on 12/10/2020. The Government seeks detention. Defense Counsel argues for release. The Court orders\nthe defendant released on Pretrial Service conditions as stated on the record. The defendant is ordered to comply with the terms and\nconditions set forth. The Court also addressed the third-party custodian as to her responsibilities. The Court orders the defendant's release\nis delayed until 12/11/2020 at 8:00 a.m.The defendant is ordered to appear for the next hearing on 12/17/2020 at 2:00 p.m. before\nMagistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone. Government Counsel: David Gappa - via video present. Defense Counsel: Roger Nutall - via video\npresent. Pretrial Services: Jessica McConville - via video present. Custody Status: In custody - via video present. Court Reporter/CD\nNumber: Karen Hooven - via video present. (Gonzales, V) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/10/2020)\n12/10/2020 7 ORDER SETTING CONDITIONS of RELEASE as to MONICO ERICH GASTELO, signed by Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone on\n12/10/2020. (Martin-Gill, S) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/11/2020)\n12/10/2020 8 APPEARANCE AND COMPLIANCE BOND/ORDER as to Monico Erich Gastelo, signed by Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone on\n12/10/2020. (Martin-Gill, S) [1:20-mj-00143-SKO] (Entered: 12/11/2020)\n12/17/2020 9 INDICTMENT as to Monico Gastelo (1) count(s) 1, 2. (Attachments: # 1 True Bill) (Rivera, O) (Entered: 12/17/2020)\n12/17/2020 10 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Release of Discovery by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 12/17/2020)\n12/17/2020 11 NOTICE of ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Roger Taylor Nuttall appearing for Monico Gastelo. Attorney Nuttall, Roger Taylor added.\n(Nuttall, Roger) (Entered: 12/17/2020)\n12/17/2020 12 ORDER (TEXT ONLY) signed by Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone on 12/17/2020 as to defendant Monico Erich Gastelo: Pursuant to\nthe Due Process Protections Act, the court hereby orders counsel for the government to satisfy its discovery and disclosure obligations,\nincluding but not limited to its obligations under Brady v. Maryland, 373 U.S. 83 (1963), and its progeny. Failure to do so may result in\nconsequences such as the dismissal of the indictment or information, dismissal of individual charges, exclusion of evidence or witnesses,\nadverse jury instructions, contempt proceedings, and sanctions by the court. (Hernandez, M) (Entered: 12/17/2020)\n12/17/2020 13 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held via video conference before Magistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone: ARRAIGNMENT AND\nPLEA RE INDICTMENT as to Monico Gastelo (1) Count 1,2 held on 12/17/2020. Defendant Monico Gastelo consents to appearing by\ntelephone. The defendant is advised of the charges and rights, waived reading, NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED. Denied the forfeiture\nallegations. Discovery to be produced within 2 weeks from today's hearing. Reciprocal discovery due within 3 weeks from today's\nhearing. Status Conference set for 2/10/2021 at 01:00 PM in Courtroom 8 (BAM) before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. The\ndefendant is ordered to appear at the next hearing. XT Start: 12/17/2020 Stop: 2/10/2021, Time is to be excluded under the Speedy Trial\nAct in that good cause exists and that the ends of justice outweigh the interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. For the\nreasons set forth on the record, the continuance requested is granted for good cause and the Court finds the ends of justice outweigh the\ninterest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. Excludable started as to Monico Gastelo: XT Start: 12/17/2020 Stop: 2/10/2021\nThe court instructed government counsel under Rule 5(f) to comply with its disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Government\nCounsel: David Gappa via video present. Defense Counsel: Roger Nuttall via video present. Custody Status: (B) via phone. Court\nReporter/CD Number: Karen Hooven via video. (Hernandez, M) (Entered: 12/17/2020)\n12/18/2020 14 STIPULATION and PROTECTIVE ORDER Between the United State and Defendant Regarding Production and Review of Protected\nInformation, as to Erich Gastelo, signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 12/18/2020. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 12/18/2020)\n01/11/2021 15 ARREST WARRANT RETURNED Executed on 12/8/2020 as to Monico Gastelo. (Marrujo, C) (Entered: 01/12/2021)\n01/19/2021 16 MOTION to MODIFY CONDITIONS of RELEASE by Monico Gastelo. Motion Hearing set for 2/2/2021 at 02:00 PM in Courtroom 7\n(SKO) before Magistrate Judge Sheila K. Oberto. (Nuttall, Roger) (Entered: 01/19/2021)\n01/25/2021 17 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on February 10, 2021. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, February 3, 2021. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 1/25/2021. (Valdez,\nE) (Entered: 01/25/2021)\n01/26/2021 18 OPPOSITION by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 01/26/2021)\n01/29/2021 19 REPLY by Monico Gastelo to RESPONSE to 16 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release. (Nuttall, Roger) (Entered: 01/29/2021)\n02/02/2021 20 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held via video conference before Magistrate Judge Sheila K. Oberto: MOTION TO MODIFY\nCONDITIONS OF RELEASE as to Monico Gastelo held on 2/2/2021. The Court noted the hearing was being conducted via video\nconference pursuant to General Order 614 and 620 and the CARES Act. Defendant and counsel consented to the appearance by video. The\nCourt heard argument in regards to the pending motion. The matter was submitted and the Court DENIED the Motion for the reasons\nstated on the record. Government Counsel: David Gappa present. Defense Counsel: Alexandria De La Fuente & Roger Nuttall present.\nCustody Status: O/R - (Telephonic). Court Reporter: Karen Hooven. (Kusamura, W) (Entered: 02/02/2021)\n02/03/2021 21 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to April 14, 2021 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n02/03/2021)\n02/04/2021 22 STIPULUATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by\nMagistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 2/4/2021. It is so ordered that the status conference is continued from February 10, 2021, to\nApril 14, 2021, at 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. The Court has reviewed and considered the stipulation\nfiled by the parties on February 3, 2021, and also reviewed the record of this case. For the reasons stated in the stipulation, the period of\ntime from February 10, 2021, to April 14, 2021, inclusive, is deemed excludable under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A) and 3161(h)(7)(B)(i),\n(ii) and (iv) because it results from a continuance granted by the Court at the request of the parties on the basis of the Courts finding that\nthe ends of justice served by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. (Valdez, E)\n(Entered: 02/04/2021)\n03/29/2021 23 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on April 14, 2021. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, April 7, 2021. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 3/29/2021. (Valdez, E)\n(Entered: 03/29/2021)\n04/07/2021 24 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to June 9, 2021 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n04/07/2021)\n04/07/2021 25 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 4/7/2021. It is so ordered that that the status conference is continued from April 14, 2021, to June 9, 2021,\nat 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. The Court has reviewed and considered the stipulation filed by the parties\non April 7, 2021, and also reviewed the record of this case. For the reasons stated in the stipulation, the period of time from April 14,\n2021, to June 9, 2021, inclusive, is deemed excludable under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A) and 3161(h)(7)(B)(i), (ii) and (iv) because it\nresults from a continuance granted by the Court at the request of the parties on the basis of the Court's finding that the ends of justice\nserved by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 04/07/2021)\n05/25/2021 26 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on June 9, 2021. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, June 2, 2021. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 5/25/2021. (Valdez, E)\n(Entered: 05/25/2021)\n06/01/2021 27 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to September 8, 2021 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n06/01/2021)\n06/01/2021 28 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 6/1/2021. It is so ordered that the status conference is continued from June 9, 2021, to September 8, 2021,\nat 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed\non June 1, 2021. Based on the reasons articulated in that filing, the court finds good cause to move the current status conference from June\n9, 2021, to September 8, 2021, and to exclude time under the Speedy Trial Act under 18 U.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)(iv), because it\nresults from a continuance granted by the court at defendant's request on the basis of the court's finding that the ends of justice served by\ntaking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 06/01/2021)\n08/23/2021 29 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on September 8, 2021. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, September 1, 2021. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 8/23/2021.\n(Valdez, E) (Entered: 08/23/2021)\n08/24/2021 30 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to November 10, 2021 by USA. (Gappa, David)\n(Entered: 08/24/2021)\n08/25/2021 31 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 8/25/2021. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed on August 24, 2021.\nThe status conference is continued from September 8, 2021, to November 10, 2021, at 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A.\nMcAuliffe. Based on the reasons articulated in that filing, the court finds good cause to move the current status conference from\nSeptember 8, 2021, to November 10, 2021, and to exclude time under the Speedy Trial Act under 18 U.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)(iv),\nbecause it results from a continuance granted by the court at defendant's request on the basis of the court's finding that the ends of justice\nserved by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 08/25/2021)\n10/27/2021 32 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on November 10, 2021. At least one week before the hearing\nthe parties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, November 3, 2021. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 10/27/2021.\n(Valdez, E) (Entered: 10/27/2021)\n10/29/2021 33 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to February 9, 2022 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n10/29/2021)\n11/01/2021 34 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 11/1/2021. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed on October 29,\n2021. Based on the reasons articulated in that filing, the court finds good cause to move the current status conference from November 10,\n2021, to February 9, 2022 at 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuilffe, and to exclude time under the Speedy Trial\nAct under 18 U.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)(iv), because it results from a continuance granted by the court at defendant's request on the\nbasis of the court's finding that the ends of justice served by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in\na speedy trial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 11/01/2021)\n01/26/2022 35 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on February 9, 2022. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, February 2, 2022, so that the Court may have sufficient time to coordinate inmate movement in the jail(s).\nMinute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 1/26/2022. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 01/26/2022)\n02/02/2022 36 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to April 27, 2022 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n02/02/2022)\n02/02/2022 37 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 2/2/2022. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed on February 2, 2022.\nBased on the reasons articulated in that filing, the court finds good cause to move the current status conference from February 9, 2022, to\nApril 27, 2022 at 1:00 pm before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe, and to exclude time under the Speedy Trial Act under 18\nU.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)(iv), because it results from a continuance granted by the court at defendant's request on the basis of the\ncourt's finding that the ends of justice served by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy\ntrial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 02/02/2022)\n04/12/2022 38 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on April 27, 2022. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. The stipulation must be filed no\nlater than noon on Wednesday, April 20, 2022, so that the Court may have sufficient time to coordinate inmate movement in the jail(s).\nMinute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 4/12/2022. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 04/12/2022)\n04/20/2022 39 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER for Continuance of Status Conference to July 13, 2022 by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n04/20/2022)\n04/20/2022 40 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act, as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 4/20/2022. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed on April 19, 2022.\nThe status conference is continued from April 27, 2022, to July 13, 2022, at 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe.\nBased on the reasons articulated in that filing, the court finds good cause to move the current status conference from April 27, 2022, to\nJuly 13, 2022, and to exclude time under the Speedy Trial Act under 18 U.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)(iv), because it results from a\ncontinuance granted by the court at defendant's request on the basis of the court's finding that the ends of justice served by taking such\naction outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 04/20/2022)\n06/22/2022 41 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on July 13, 2022. At least one week before the hearing the\nparties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. However, in any request for a\ncontinuance, the parties shall explain when they will be ready to set a trial date. The stipulation must be filed no later than noon on\nWednesday, July 6, 2022, so that the Court may have sufficient time to coordinate inmate movement in the jail(s). Minute order signed by\nMagistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 6/22/2022. (Valdez, E) (Entered: 06/22/2022)\n07/06/2022 42 STIPULATION regarding excludable time periods under speedy trial act. (Attachments: # 1 Proposed Order Will email order as well)\n(Nuttall, Roger) (Entered: 07/06/2022)\n07/07/2022 43 STIPULATION and ORDER Regarding Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act as to Monico Gastelo (1), signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 7/7/2022. It is so ordered that the status conference is continued from July 13, 2022, to September 14,\n2022, at 1:00 p.m. before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. Time is excluded pursuant to 18 U.S.C.\u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), and (B)\n(iv). (Rivera, O) (Entered: 07/07/2022)\n08/22/2022 44 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): This case is set for a status conference on September 14, 2022. At least one week before the hearing\nthe parties shall file a joint status report informing the court of the status of the case, including whether any change of plea is anticipated, a\nproposed next date for a status conference or change of plea, and whether defendant agrees to exclude time to the next date. Alternatively,\nthe parties may stipulate to a continuance of the status conference, with an appropriate exclusion of time. If the parties do not resolve the\ncase in advanced of the next status conference, they shall be prepared to set a trial date at the status conference hearing. The\nstipulation must be filed no later than noon on Wednesday, September 7, 2022, so that the Court may have sufficient time to coordinate\ninmate movement in the jail(s). If unforeseen circumstances delay the timely submission of the stipulation, the AUSA is instructed to\nemail the courtroom deputy. Minute order signed by Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 8/22/2022. (Valdez, E) (Entered:\n08/22/2022)\n08/24/2022 45 ORDER REASSIGNING CASE by Chief Judge Kimberly J. Mueller: Due to the appointment of *District Judge Ana de Alba* to the\nbench of the Eastern District of California, this action is reassigned from *District Judge Dale A. Drozd* to District Judge Ana de Alba for\nall further proceedings. (Gonzalez, R) (Entered: 08/24/2022)\n09/14/2022 46 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held via video conference before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe: STATUS\nCONFERENCE as to Monico Gastelo (1) held on 9/14/2022. The Court noted the hearing was conducted via video conference pursuant to\nGeneral Order 614, 620, 624, 628, 630, 632, 635, 640, 649 & 652 and the CARES Act. Defendant and counsel consented to the\nappearance by video. The Court received and reviewed the letter from Attorney Nuttall's physician. Discussion held regarding negotiations\nand counsel's availability. Parties requested another status conference and waived excludable time - So Ordered, 18 USC 3161. Status\nConference set for 12/14/2022 at 01:00 PM in Courtroom 8 (BAM) before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. Excludable\nstarted as to Monico Gastelo: XT Start: 9/14/2022 Stop: 12/14/2022. Time is to be excluded under the Speedy Trial Act in that good cause\nexists and that the ends of justice outweigh the interest of the public and the defendant in a speedy trial. For the reasons set forth on the\nrecord, the continuance requested is granted for good cause and the Court finds the ends of justice outweigh the interest of the public and\nthe defendant in a speedy trial. Government Counsel: David Gappa - present via zoom. Defense Counsel: Harry Drandell for Roger\nNuttall - present via zoom. Custody Status: BOND - present via zoom. Court Reporter/CD Number: ECRO