Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 2/24/2025. (Deputy Clerk EV) (Entered: 02/24/2025)\n02/24/2025 84 MOTION to CONTINUE TRIAL by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 02/24/2025)\n03/03/2025 85 OPPOSITION by USA to 84 Motion to Continue. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 03/03/2025)\n03/04/2025 86 MINUTE ORDER (TEXT ONLY): On February 24, 2025, defense counsel filed a Motion to Continue Trial (Doc. 84 ). On March 3, 2025,\nthe government filed an Opposition (Doc. 85 ). Pursuant to the request of counsel the Court SETS a Motion to Continue Trial on\n3/12/2025 at 1:00 PM in Courtroom 8 (BAM) before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe. Minute order signed by Magistrate\nJudge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 3/4/2025. (Deputy Clerk EV) (Entered: 03/04/2025)\n03/12/2025 87 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe: STATUS CONFERENCE and MOTION to\nContinue Trial as to Monico Gastelo (1) held on 3/12/2025. The Court received and reviewed the motion and opposition. Motion argued &\nsubmitted - MOTION DENIED. The jury trial date of 4/22/2025 was confirmed. Government Counsel: David Gappa - present. Defense\nCounsel: Roger Wilson - present. Custody Status: BOND - present. Court Reporter/CD Number: ECRO - Otilia Rosales. (Deputy Clerk\nEV) (Entered: 03/13/2025)\n03/14/2025 88 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER Resetting Trial Date and Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act by USA. (Gappa,\nDavid) (Entered: 03/14/2025)\n03/14/2025 89 STIPULATION and ORDER Resetting Trial Date and Excludable Time Periods Under Speedy Trial Act as to Monico Gastelo (1) signed\nby Magistrate Judge Barbara A. McAuliffe on 3/14/2025. The court has reviewed and considered the stipulation that the parties filed on\nMarch 14, 2025. This case is rescheduled for a trial beginning on May 27, 2025, at 8:30 a.m. before the Honorable John C.\nCoughenour, Senior United States District Court Judge for the Western District of Washington. By separate order, this case will be\nreassigned to District Judge Coughenour. The trial will take place in the United States Courthouse for the Eastern District of California in\nFresno. The jury trial date of April 22, 2025, and trial confirmation date of April 7, 2025, are vacated. For the reasons stated in the\nstipulation, the period of time from April 22, 2025, through May 27, 2025, inclusive, is deemed excludable under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 3161(h)(7)\n(A) and 3161(h)(7)(B)(i), (ii) and (iv) because it results from a continuance granted by the court at the request of the parties on the basis of\nthe court's finding that the ends of justice served by taking such action outweigh the best interest of the public and the defendant in a\nspeedy trial. (Deputy Clerk EV) (Entered: 03/14/2025)\n03/14/2025 90 ORDER signed by Chief Judge Troy L. Nunley: Due to the Order of Designation of Senior District Judge John C. Coughenour for Service\nin Another District within the Ninth Circuit, this action is REASSIGNED to Senior District Judge John C. Coughenour for all further\nproceedings. The case number on all future filed documents shall be: 1:20-cr-0252 JCC BAM. (TEXT ONLY ENTRY) (Deputy Clerk\nJJD) (Entered: 03/14/2025)\n03/18/2025 91 MINUTE ORDER (Text Only Entry) as to Monico Gastelo signed by Senior Judge John C. Coughenour on 3/18/2025: This matter comes\nbefore the Court sua sponte. Several dates and deadlines were previously set in this matter, (see Dkt. No. 75 ), some of which were then\nvacated and/or reset, (see Dkt. No. 89 at 4). In light of the recent reassignment of this matter to this Court, (see Dkt. No. 90 ), and the\nresulting new trial date of May 27, 2025, the Court resets remaining pretrial deadlines as follows: Motions in limine (if any) must be\npresented in a joint brief by May 8, 2025. Trial briefs are due May 13, 2025. Exhibit and witness lists, proposed jury instructions, a verdict\nform, and voir dire are due by May 13, 2025. As to the form of each, Counsel should consult the Court's chambers procedures website for\ninstructions, available at https://www.wawd.uscourts.gov/judges/coughenour-procedures#coughenour6. There will be no separate trial\nconfirmation hearing. The Court will decide any motions in limine by oral rulings the morning of trial. (Deputy Clerk PVY) (Entered:\n03/18/2025)\n04/29/2025 92 NOTICE of Expert Disclosure by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 04/29/2025)\n05/08/2025 93 MOTION IN LIMINE by USA as to Monico Gastelo. Motion Hearing set for 5/27/2025 at 08:30 AM in Courtroom 5 before Senior Judge\nJohn C. Coughenour. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/08/2025)\n05/08/2025 94 NOTICE of ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: McKenzie Hightower, GOVT on behalf of USA. Attorney Hightower, McKenzie added.\n(Hightower, McKenzie) (Entered: 05/08/2025)\n05/12/2025 95 NOTICE of Amended Bill of Particulars for Forfeiture of Property by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/12/2025)\n05/13/2025 96 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER Erich Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/13/2025)\n05/13/2025 97 STIPULATION AND ORDER TO CONTINUE JURY TRIAL as to Monico Gastelo signed by Senior Judge John C. Coughenour on\n5/13/2025. IT IS SO ORDERED that the jury trial set for May 27, 2025, be continued to May 28, 2025, at 8:30 a.m. in Courtroom 5\nbefore the District Judge John C. Coughenour. Time is excluded pursuant to 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 3161(h)(7)(A), B(iv). (Deputy Clerk YV)\n(Entered: 05/13/2025)\n05/13/2025 98 STIPULATION and PROPOSED ORDER MONICO ERICH GASTELO. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/13/2025)\n05/13/2025 99 STIPULATION AND ORDER TO EXTEND PRETRIAL DEADLINES as to Monico Gastelo signed by Senior Judge John C.\nCoughenour on 5/13/2025. IT IS SO ORDERED that the May 13, 2025, pretrial filing deadline for trial briefs, exhibit and witness lists,\nproposed jury instructions, a verdict form and voir dire, be extended to May 14, 2025. (Deputy Clerk YV) (Entered: 05/13/2025)\n05/14/2025 100 TRIAL BRIEF by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 101 WITNESS LIST by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 102 TRIAL EXHIBIT by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 103 PROPOSED VOIR DIRE by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 104 PROPOSED VOIR DIRE by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 105 EXHIBIT LIST by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 106 WITNESS LIST by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 107 TRIAL BRIEF by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 108 PROPOSED JURY INSTRUCTIONS by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 109 PROPOSED JURY INSTRUCTIONS by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 110 PROPOSED VERDICT submitted by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/27/2025 111 MINUTE ORDER (Text Only Entry) Pursuant to email from defense counsel on May 25, 2025 at 12:21pm to the Court: Jury trial as to\nMonico Gastelo currently set for Wednesday, 5/28/2025 is VACATED. Change of Plea Hearing as to Monico Gastelo set for Wednesday,\n5/28/2025 at 11:00 AM in Courtroom 4 (JLT) before District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on\nMay 27, 2025. (Deputy Clerk IM) (Entered: 05/27/2025)\n05/28/2025 112 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held before District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston: CHANGE of PLEA HEARING as to Monico\nGastelo held on 5/28/2025. Oath Given. Monico Gastelo (1) entered GUILTY PLEA on Counts 1 and 2. Sentencing set for 9/8/2025 at\n09:00 AM in Courtroom 4 (JLT) before District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston. Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the U.S.\nMarshal forthwith. Defense counsel shall file DEFENDANT'S WAIVER OF RIGHTSAND FACTUAL BASIS IN SUPPORT OF PLEAS\nforthwith. Government Counsel: David Gappa, McKenzie Hightower present. Defense Counsel: Roger Wilson present. Custody Status:\nBOND. Court Reporter/CD Number: Rachel Lundy. (Deputy Clerk IM) (Entered: 05/28/2025)\n05/28/2025 113 PLEA AGREEMENT as to Monico Gastelo. Attorney Wilson, Roger Dale added. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 05/28/2025)\n07/29/2025 114 (TO BE VIEWED BY ASSIGNED COUNSEL ONLY) DISCLOSED PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT (DRAFT) as to Monico\nGastelo. Informal objections shall not be submitted via CM/ECF and shall be in compliance with the sentencing schedule and pursuant to\nLocal Rule 461. (Corona, S) (Entered: 07/29/2025)\n08/18/2025 115 SENTENCING PRESENTENCE INVESTIGATION REPORT (FINAL) as to Monico Gastelo. (Attachments: # 1 Sentencing\nRecommendation, # 2 Objection Letter - Defense, # 3 Response to Defense Objections)(Head, Sarah) (Entered: 08/18/2025)\n08/18/2025 116 MOTION to CONTINUE SENTENCING by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 08/18/2025)\n08/21/2025 117 OPPOSITION by USA. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 08/21/2025)\n08/21/2025 118 MINUTE ORDER (Text Only Entry) The Court has reviewed the defense motion to continue the sentencing hearing (Doc. 116) and the\ngovernment's response (Doc. 117). This matter has been set for sentencing for months--since May 28, 2025 (Doc. 113). The draft PSR was\nissued on July 29, 2025, to which the defense filed objections (Doc. 115-2) on August 11, 2025. The probation officer responded to the\nobjections on the same day (Doc. 115-3). One of the objections addresses a 5-level enhancement. Defense attorney, Wilson, indicates he\nwill have insufficient time to prepare for the sentencing hearing. The government oppose the continuance request because an attorney from\nout of the area will be travelling to the sentencing hearing and due to the prolonged upset this will cause the victim. The Court is\nsympathetic to the unnecessary costs imposed on the government due to Mr. Wilson's schedule, which does not allow him to prepare more\nquickly. However, the defendant's right to prepared counsel overwhelms the government's expense. Likewise, the Court acknowledges that\ncase has languished and this must place an emotional toll on the victim. As difficult as it will be for the victim, the the Court will GRANT\nthe continuance. However, Mr. Wilson SHALL prioritize this case so he can be prepared for the sentencing on 11/17/2025 at 9 a.m. As Mr.\nWilson points out, his client is facing a possible long prison term. He deserves prepared counsel who gives this case the attention it\ndeserves signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on August 21, 2025. (Deputy Clerk IM) (Entered: 08/21/2025)\n11/12/2025 119 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered: 11/12/2025)\n11/12/2025 120 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM by Monico Gastelo. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 11/12/2025)\n11/13/2025 121 APPLICATION for Preliminary Order of Forfeiture and Publication Thereof by USA as to Monico Gastelo (Attachments: # 1 Proposed\nOrder for Preliminary Order of Forfeiture)(Gappa, David) (Entered: 11/13/2025)\n11/13/2025 122 MOTION for FORFEITURE of PROPERTY and Notice of Motion for Preliminary Order of Forfeiture as to Real Property Located at\n1604 N. Farris Avenue, Fresno, California by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Attachments: # 1 United States' Motion and Application for\nPreliminary Order of Forfeiture Against Defendant Monico Gastelo as to Real Property Located at 1604 N. Farris Avenue, Fresno,\nCalifornia, # 2 Proposed Order for Preliminary Order of Forfeiture as to Real Property Located at 1604 N. Farris Avenue, Fresno,\nCalifornia)(Gappa, David) (Entered: 11/13/2025)\n11/14/2025 123 PRELIMINARY ORDER of FORFEITURE, signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on 11/14/2025 as to Monico Gastelo. (Deputy\nClerk CM) (Entered: 11/14/2025)\n11/17/2025 124 PROPOSED ORDER re Forfeiture Money Judgment and Application by USA as to Monico Gastelo. (Gappa, David) (Entered:\n11/17/2025)\n11/17/2025 125 MINUTES (Text Only) for proceedings held before District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston: SENTENCING held on 11/17/2025 for Monico\nGastelo (1) CUSTODY: 300 months on Count 1, and 180 months on Count 2, to be served consecutively to each other for a total term of\n480 months Special Assessment $200. SUPERVISED RELEASE: 180 months on Count 1, 180 months on Count 2, all to be served\nconcurrently for a total term of 180 months with conditions. Mandatory drug testing suspended. Prison: Terminal Island, CA. Counsel will\nprovide stipulation regarding USA motion for forfeiture. Defendant waives his right and stated on the record. Other monetary penalties\ndefer within 90 days or sooner at the request of counsel. DEFENDANT TERMINATED. CASE CLOSED. Government Counsel: David\nGappa, McKenzie Hightower present. Defense Counsel: Roger Wilson present. Custody Status: CUSTODY. Court Reporter/CD Number:\nECRO. Certified Court Interpreter: Javier Avelar, Language: Spanish-Oath on File. (Deputy Clerk IM) (Entered: 11/18/2025)\n11/18/2025 126 APPLICATION AND ORDER FOR FORFEITURE MONEY JUDGMENT signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on November\n18, 2025. (Deputy Clerk IM) (Entered: 11/18/2025)\n11/24/2025 127 JUDGMENT and COMMITMENT signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on November 24, 2025 as to Monico Gastelo. (Deputy\nClerk IM) (Entered: 11/24/2025)\n11/26/2025 128 NOTICE of APPEAL by Monico Gastelo re 127 Judgment and Commitment. (Wilson, Roger) (Entered: 11/26/2025)\n11/26/2025 129 APPEAL PROCESSED to Ninth Circuit re 128 Notice of Appeal filed by Monico Gastelo. Filed dates for Notice of Appeal *11/26/2025*,\nComplaint *12/8/2020* and Appealed Order / Judgment *11/24/2025*. Court Reporter: *ECRO*. *Fee Status: CJA or IFP granted on\n12/29/2022* (Attachments: # 1 Appeal Information) (Deputy Clerk OFR) (Entered: 11/26/2025)\n11/26/2025 130 USCA CASE NUMBER 25-7471 for 128 Notice of Appeal filed by Monico Gastelo. (Deputy Clerk OFR) (Entered: 11/26/2025)\n12/17/2025 131 USCA ORDER as to 128 Notice of Appeal filed by Monico Gastelo. The motion to withdraw and to appoint new counsel is granted.\n(Deputy Clerk CRM) (Entered: 12/17/2025)\n12/19/2025 132 ORDER APPOINTING Counsel, signed by District Judge Jennifer L. Thurston on 12/19/2025 as to Monico Gastelo. Added Attorney\nAndrea Renee St. Julian for Monico Gastelo. (Deputy Clerk CRM) (Entered: 12/19/2025)\n12/28/2025 133 TRANSCRIPT REQUEST for proceedings held on 12/09/2020; 12/10/2020; 12/17/2020; 02/02/2021; 09/14/2022; 12/14/2022;\n03/12/2025; 05/28/2025; 11/17/2025 before Judge Stanley A. Boone; Sheila K. Oberto; Barbara A. McAuliffe; Jennifer L. Thurston.\nMULTIPLE REPORTERS REQUESTED (St. Julian, Andrea) (Entered: 12/28/2025)\n01/26/2026 134 TRANSCRIPT of Proceedings as to Monico Gastelo held on 05-28-2025, Change of Plea Hearing, before District Judge Jennifer L.\nThurston, filed by Court Reporter Rachael Lundy, Phone number 559-207-1072 E-mail rlundy.csr@gmail.com. Transcript may be viewed\nat the court public terminal or purchased through the Court Reporter/Transcriber before the deadline for Release of Transcript Restriction.\nAfter that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of Intent to Request Redaction must be filed within 5 court days.\nRedaction Request due 2/17/2026. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 2/26/2026. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 4/27/2026.\n(Deputy Clerk rl) (Entered: 01/26/2026)\n01/28/2026 135 TRANSCRIPT REQUEST for proceedings held on 12/9/2020, 12/10/2020, 12/17/2020, 2/2/2021, 9/14/2022, 12/14/2022, 3/12/2025,\n5/28/2025, 11/17/2025 before Judge Boone,Thurston,McAuliffe,Oberto. MULTIPLE REPORTERS REQUESTED (Gappa, David)\n(Entered: 01/28/2026)\n02/02/2026 136 TRANSCRIPT of Proceedings as to Monico Gastelo held on 12-9-20, INITIAL APPEARANCE before Magistrate Judge Stanley A.\nBoone, filed by Court Reporter Karen Hooven, Phone number 559-264-0584 E-mail khoovencsr@gmail.com. Transcript may be viewed at\nthe court public terminal or purchased through the Court Reporter/Transcriber before the deadline for Release of Transcript Restriction.\nAfter that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of Intent to Request Redaction must be filed within 5 court days.\nRedaction Request due 2/23/2026. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 3/5/2026. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 5/4/2026.\n(Hooven, Karen) (Entered: 02/02/2026)\n02/02/2026 137 TRANSCRIPT of Proceedings as to Monico Gastelo held on 12-10-20, DETENTION HEARING before Magistrate Judge Stanley A.\nBoone, filed by Court Reporter Karen Hooven, Phone number 559-264-0584 E-mail khoovencsr@gmail.com. Transcript may be viewed at\nthe court public terminal or purchased through the Court Reporter/Transcriber before the deadline for Release of Transcript Restriction.\nAfter that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of Intent to Request Redaction must be filed within 5 court days.\nRedaction Request due 2/23/2026. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 3/5/2026. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 5/4/2026.\n(Hooven, Karen) (Entered: 02/02/2026)\n02/02/2026 138 TRANSCRIPT of Proceedings as to Monico Gastelo held on 12-17-20, ARRAIGNMENT AND PLEA RE INDICTMENT before\nMagistrate Judge Stanley A. Boone, filed by Court Reporter Karen Hooven, Phone number 559-264-0584 E-mail khoovencsr@gmail.com.\nTranscript may be viewed at the court public terminal or purchased through the Court Reporter/Transcriber before the deadline for Release\nof Transcript Restriction. After that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of Intent to Request Redaction must be filed\nwithin 5 court days. Redaction Request due 2/23/2026. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 3/5/2026. Release of Transcript Restriction\nset for 5/4/2026. (Hooven, Karen) (Entered: 02/02/2026)\n02/02/2026 139 TRANSCRIPT of Proceedings as to Monico Gastelo held on 2-2-21, MOTION TO MODIFY CONDITIONS OF RELEASE before\nMagistrate Judge Sheila K. Oberto, filed by Court Reporter Karen Hooven, Phone